<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Baean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I have had the game since April, where I payed full price, 70$.  Including this month, I have paid another 70$ in monthly fees.  Shouldn't I get a deal on the RoK?  I know Verant says the expansion is optional, well, another 70$ is not an option.  Are there any plans to give us current EQ gamers a discount?  Say a 10$ fee that we can pay over the internet - a-la UO?<P>Baean</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Moonshadow</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Actually because the expansion will not be playable without EQ I can't see that happening.<P>In the debate over the cost of EQ, I haven't seen anyone mention value yet.<P>I am accustomed to purchasing one or two games per month.  Since EQ I have not bought any.  For me, EQ is a great value and I'll certainly be investing in the Ruins of Kunark, but if it's not a worthy investment for <B>YOU</B> nothing changes... except perhaps your zones get a little emptier as players move to Kunark.<P>So, buy the expansion or not, you can't lose.<P>Just my 2cp.<P><P>------------------<BR><I>Moonshadow Litherial</I><BR>Companions of the Gate<BR>Bristlebane<BR><I>Galdarya </I>- The Hand of Evil<BR>Rallos Zek<BR><B><I>Working together for a better Norrath</B></I><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Tathsis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Aye, EQ has provided me with more gaming fun for my buck than ANY other game that I have ever played (well, quake ctf probably comes close).<P>I do not begrudge Verant my $50 USD initial purchase or my $80 USD maintainance fee.<P>Nor will I bedgrudge them $20 - $30 USD for the expansion.<P>It has been well worth the money, even if I do occasionlly have complaints.<P>-Tathsis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kadmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">In one of the press releases Verant did comment on this.  It stated that the pricing structure would most likely follow that of UO's expansion.  For those that don't know how UO did it.  Those that don't have the game, will be able to get EQ and ROK in one package at normal price.  Those that have EQ should be able to get ROK for about 7-10 dollars.  Enough to handle the manufactioning and distribution of the CD.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">SoulThief</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well... i just had to comment on this subject.  EQ has provided me with so many hours of great gameplay.  Even UO didn't entertain me as much.  <P>But, i don't know about everyone else... i payed $50 for the game.  Everywhere i went it costed about $50.  I just don't see it costing $70 like the person who started this topic said.  I dunno... i just find it kind of hard to believe.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Why pay for something when you can take it for free?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Moonshadow</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"> <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"> Canadians SoulThief.  The game is $70 in Canada due to the exchange.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Leafwind-Ranger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Lucky me, I payed $38.50. U.S.<P>There was a question last week I think when I logged on, "would you download the ruins of kunark if given the chance? 600 mb file"<P>It might have been stated differently, but you get the idea. I, myself, play maybe 3-10 hrs a week. EQ has been the game I've always wanted, roleplaying, adventuring, fighting(kinda') and quests.<P>Although I wish you could gain xp at a better rate doing something besides fighting. I will buy the expansion, I'm sure, just because I'm a ranger and I love to wander!<BR>If only the $7 to $10 price was correct, MAN! whatta deal!<P>------------------<BR>Leafwind<BR>Wood Elf Ranger<BR>Quellious<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Daemius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well I just noticed this post on EQ Stratics <BR>"Just heard that Electronics Boutique has started taking pre-orders for the EverQuest Expansion, Ruins of Kunark. It costs right at $40 and, according to my pre-order receipt, it'll be in on March 21."<P>So much for the $10-$20 dollars most people thought it would be. Granted I know I will still buy it, but I see that as being very expensive for an expansion. And pre-ordering is supposed to be cheaper. I guess that means those who do not pre-order will be paying about $50 or so at the retail store.<P>Well since they do have (IMHO) the best Multi-player RPG out there they can do about anything they want. But the price still stinks.<P>Just my two cents, curious to hear what others think.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Artereis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This was posted on EQVault:<P>&gt;The product being advertised is the entire &gt;game plus the Expansion for new users. The &gt;Expansion for existing users will be &gt;offered to you all direct and in-game and 